The `isReflexive`, `isSymmetric`, `isAntiSymmetric`, and `isTransitive` methods check whether the relation satisfies the corresponding properties.

The `isEquivalence` method checks whether the relation is an equivalence relation, which means it must be reflexive, symmetric, and transitive.

